Project 247. Trust region policy optimization
Description:
Trust Region Policy Optimization (TRPO) improves policy gradient methods by restricting the size of policy updates, ensuring each update stays within a "trust region" to avoid catastrophic performance drops. It uses constrained optimization to limit the KL divergence between old and new policies. TRPO is more stable but computationally heavier than PPO. In this project, weâ€™ll implement a simplified TRPO-style update using a library that supports it (like garage, stable-baselines3, or trpo-pytorch).

Since implementing TRPO from scratch is quite involved, we'll use a PyTorch-based TRPO implementation from the trpo-pytorch library for clarity.

